Job Summary:

This job implements tasks within the Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC), follows internal conventions and procedures, makes technical decisions, collaborates with peers and project leads, and contributes to code and design reviews.
Job Description:

Essential Responsibilities:

Implements tasks within the Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC), receiving structure and oversight from more experienced staff
Follows well-established internal conventions and standard procedures
Understands internal standards & processes an applies them to make technical decisions
Collaborates with peers, manager, and project lead to gain understanding of tasks and review solutions
May contribute to code & design reviews
Minimum Qualifications:

1+ years relevant experience and a Bachelor’s degree OR Any equivalent combination of education and experience.
Additional Responsibilities & Preferred Qualifications:

Your way to impact

At PayPal, Software Engineers are the architects of our global payment platform. You'll design, develop, and optimize core systems powering millions of transactions daily, delivering innovative solutions that delight customers and drive business success.

Your day-to-day: 

As a Software Engineer - FullStack, you will:

Craft exceptional digital experiences from the ground up. 
Collaborate with talented teams to build robust Full-stack systems. 
Create innovative Full Stack components and solutions.
Contribute to a high-performing team through code reviews and collaboration.
Master Full Stack development best practices and technologies.
What you need to bring:

2+ years of hands-on Full Stack development experience and a bachelor’s degree in computer science or related field.
Proficiency in Java, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, and at least one modern frontend framework (React/ Angular/ Vue), Node, Spring boot.
Strong problem-solving and debugging skills.
Preferred Qualifications:

Experience with GraphQL, or similar Full Stack technologies.
Understanding of responsive design and accessibility.
